eligibility_criteria.description:
Minimum age: 18 Years
Maximum age: 40 Years
COHORT A: MRI/CT must demonstrate measurable enhancing tumor of at least 1 cm^2 in cross-sectional area to allow assessment of radiographic response
Sodium < 130 mmol/L or > 155 mmol/L despite intervention to normalize levels

Patients with active infections including known human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) are not eligible; HIV positive patients on highly active anti-retroviral therapy (HAART) with undetectable blood HIV levels are eligible; patients with a history or serological evidence of exposure to hepatitis B without active infection are eligible for this study

Other concurrent severe and/or uncontrolled medical disease which would compromise participation in the study in the opinion of the investigator (e.g., uncontrolled diabetes, unstable angina, or congestive heart failure -- New York Heart Association Class III or IV)
Willing and able to provide written informed consent.
Patients should not receive immunization with attenuated live vaccines within one week of study entry or during study period

Willing and able to provide written informed consent and Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) authorization for the release of personal health information 
* NOTE: HIPAA authorization may be either included in the informed consent or obtained separately

groups.description:
IV infusion 1x Weekly for a 21 day dosing cycle
Subjects will be assigned to the recommended Phase 2 dose of 250 mg
groups.name: Phase 2 dose levels: KB004

outcome_measures.measure: Development of anti-PSA immune response defined as an increase of >= 200% above pre-immunization level of anti-PSA T cells as measured by enzyme-linked immunosorbent spot analysis

outcome_measures.analysis_method: BOR was defined as the best response across all time points from randomization until radiologically confirmed PD using RECIST, v1.1 criteria. CR was defined as the disappearance of all target and non-target lesions and any pathological lymph nodes (whether target or non-target) must have reduction in short axis to <10 mm and normalization of tumor marker level of non-target lesions. PR was defined as having a ≥30% decrease in sum of LD of target lesions. PD was defined as having a ≥20% increase in sum of LD of target lesions and ≥5 mm increase above nadir. outcome_measures.measure: Best Overall Response (BOR) of Complete Response (CR), Partial Response (PR), Stable Disease (SD) or PD
